msgid "Snapping"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:17
msgid "In Krita 3.0, we now have functionality for Grids and Guides, but of course, this functionality is by itself not that interesting without snapping."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:19
msgid "Snapping is the ability to have Krita automatically align a selection or shape to the grids and guides, document center and document edges. For Vector layers, this goes even a step further, and we can let you snap to bounding boxes, intersections, extrapolated lines and more."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:21
msgid "All of these can be toggled using the snap pop-up menu which is assigned to :kbd:`Shift + S` shortcut."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:23
msgid "Now, let us go over what each option means:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:25
msgid "Grids"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:26
msgid "This will snap the cursor to the current grid, as configured in the grid docker. This doesn’t need the grid to be visible. Grids are saved per document, making this useful for aligning your art work to grids, as is the case for game sprites and grid-based designs."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:27
msgid "Pixel"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:28
msgid "This allows to snap to every pixel under the cursor. Similar to Grid Snapping but with a grid having spacing = 1px and offset = 0px."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:30
msgid "This allows you to snap to guides, which can be dragged out from the ruler. Guides do not need to be visible for this, and are saved per document. This is useful for comic panels and similar print-layouts, though we recommend Scribus for more intensive work."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:33
msgid ".. image:: images/snapping/Snap-orthogonal.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:35
msgid "Orthogonal (Vector Only)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:35
msgid "This allows you to snap to a horizontal or vertical line from existing vector objects' nodes (Unless dealing with resizing the height or width only, in which case you can drag the cursor over the path). This is useful for aligning object horizontally or vertically, like with comic panels."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:38
msgid ".. image:: images/snapping/Snap-node.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:40
msgid "Node (Vector Only)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:40
msgid "This snaps a vector node or an object to the nodes of another path."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:43
msgid ".. image:: images/snapping/Snap-extension.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:45
msgid "Extension (Vector Only)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:45
msgid "When we draw an open path, the last nodes on either side can be mathematically extended. This option allows you to snap to that. The direction of the node depends on its side handles in path editing mode."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:48
msgid ".. image:: images/snapping/Snap-intersection.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:49
msgid "Intersection (Vector Only)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:50
msgid "This allows you to snap to an intersection of two vectors."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:51
msgid "Bounding box (Vector Only)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:52
msgid "This allows you to snap to the bounding box of a vector shape."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:53
msgid "Image bounds"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:54
msgid "Allows you to snap to the vertical and horizontal borders of an image."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:56
msgid "Image center"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/snapping.rst:56
msgid "Allows you to snap to the horizontal and vertical center of an image."
msgstr ""

